<TITLE> Juba League leader testifies </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Panchagarh, Apr 16 (bdnews24.com)  Juba League leader Liton gave a confessional statement regarding the murder of a Chhatra League leader on Thursday. Liton, one of the main accused in the case, gave the statement under Section 164 to judicial magistrate Md Mizanur Rahman. However, another accused in the case, Manju did not provide statements. Both of them were remanded for three days. Faruk Hossain, organising secretary of BCL Ward 1 of Panchagarh, was stabbed by his rivals during a clash on Apr 8 over leasing of a pond. The Juba League, is the ruling Awami League's youth wing, while the Chhatra League is its student wing. A case was filed against 16 leaders and activists of the Juba League. Police arrested five of the accused and took Liton and Manju for quizzing on Apr 12. Six activists of the ruling Awami League's youth wing were suspended recently for their involvement with the incident. Meanwhile, district Juba League president Shahidul Islam denied that Liton was a party member. Sadar police chief Md Jamiruddin said that they had acquired information about Liton's involvement in the killing. bdnews24
